snippet.textDisplay:
I appreciate that they try to give their fans what they think we want. I'm assuming that most viewers are young kids/teens. But as someone who's a bit older, I can say that while I still enjoy their content, it certainly does seem scripted and overacted much of the time. Geared more toward the young and gullible, I guess?


I began watching them a few years ago, when they were still exploring abandoned places. Hell, my first introduction to Colby was TFIL's Suicide Forest video. I remember thinking how calm and brave he seemed, leading the way almost all of the time. It was much more "real", and I liked that. I think we'd all like to see them be a little more serious; a little more adult... and less of the theatrics.


Always a fan, though.
